<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-275-520  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 275 520.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  Feb 5 1990 v4 n5 p6(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Pentagon ADP restructuring reflected in 1991 budget. (automateddata processing)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brewin, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Defense Department will cut $4.3 billion from its 1991 - 1995budgets by developing standard, department-wide systems,consolidating automated data processing centers, and fundingcost-savings programs.andP;  Automated data processing budget cuts for1991 total $288.1 million.andP;  The budget figures reflect thePentagon's new Corporate Information Management (CIM) initiative,part of the Defense Management Review ordered by Pres Bush inFebruary, 1989.andP;  The CIM plan met with some approval in Congress,which wants to see more before endorsing it fully.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     BudgetingCost ReductionUnited States. Department of Defense.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   DOD Corporate Information Management Initiative savings. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>